dcterms:description: The PhysioNet Sepsis Early Prediction Challenge 2019 dataset contains 38,803 patients, where each patient is monitored by 34 irregularly sampled sensors. Each patient is labelled by occurrence of sepsis within the next 6 hours.

dcterms:description: The PhysioNet Mortality Prediction Challenge 2012 dataset includes 11,988 patients, where each observation contains multivariate time series with 36 sensors. Each observation is associated with a binary label indicating the length of stay in ICU.
dcterms:title: P12

dcterms:creator: A. Reiss
D. Stricker
dcterms:description: The PAMAP2 Physical Activity Monitoring dataset measures daily living activities of 9 subjects with 3 inertial measurement units. It contains 5,333 segments of sensory signals, each measured by 17 sensors and labelled into 8 classes representing activities of daily living.
dcterms:title: PAM
